{"title_page": "Kalyanasundareswarar Temple, Thiruvelvikudi", "text_new": "{{coord|11.086791|79.568868|display=title}}\n[[File:Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple1.jpg|200x200px|right|The entrance of the temple|thumb]]\n'''Kalyanasundareswarar Temple''' (\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba3 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd)<ref name=\"ta.wikipedia.org\">[[:ta:\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba3 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd]]</ref> is a [[Hindu temple]] located at [[Thiruvelvikudi]] in the [[Kuthalam taluk]] of [[Mayiladuthurai district]] of [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. It is dedicated to [[Shiva]].\n\n== Deity ==\n\nThe presiding deity is Kalyanasundareswarar and the consort is Parimala Sugantha Nayaki.\n\n== Significance ==\n\nHymns have been composed in praise of the temple by [[Sambandar]] and [[Sundarar]] in the ''[[Thevaram]]''. Sundarar is believed to have bathed in the Agni theertham at this spot to cure himself. Thiruvelvikudi was also the place where Shiva granted half of his body to [[Parvathi]] making Thiruvelvikudi the birthplace of the [[Ardhanarisvara]] cult.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web|title=Kalyana Sundareswarar Temple|url=http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=234|work=[[Dinamalar]]}}\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple2.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple3.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple4.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple5.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple6.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple7.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Mayiladuthurai district]]\n[[Category:Padal Petra Stalam]]\n\n{{India-Hindu-temple-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{coord|11.086791|79.568868|display=title}}\n[[File:Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple1.jpg|200x200px|right|The entrance of the temple|thumb]]\n'''Kalyanasundareswarar Temple''' (\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba3 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd)<ref name=\"ta.wikipedia.org\">[[:ta:\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba3 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd]]</ref> is a [[Hindu temple]] located at [[Thiruvelvikudi]] in the [[Kuthalam taluk]] of [[Nagapattinam district]] of [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. It is dedicated to [[Shiva]].\n\n== Deity ==\n\nThe presiding deity is Kalyanasundareswarar and the consort is Parimala Sugantha Nayaki.\n\n== Significance ==\n\nHymns have been composed in praise of the temple by [[Sambandar]] and [[Sundarar]] in the ''[[Thevaram]]''. Sundarar is believed to have bathed in the Agni theertham at this spot to cure himself. Thiruvelvikudi was also the place where Shiva granted half of his body to [[Parvathi]] making Thiruvelvikudi the birthplace of the [[Ardhanarisvara]] cult.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{cite web|title=Kalyana Sundareswarar Temple|url=http://temple.dinamalar.com/en/new_en.php?id=234|work=[[Dinamalar]]}}\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple2.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple3.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple4.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple5.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple6.jpg|\nFile: Tiruvelvikkudi kalyana sundaresvarar temple7.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n[[Category:Shiva temples in Nagapattinam district]]\n[[Category:Padal Petra Stalam]]